.TH SYSMONITOR 1 "May 2025" "version 1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sysmonitor \- interactive system monitor and logger with GUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysmonitor.sh
[\fIOPTION\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsysmonitor.sh\fR is an interactive Bash script that displays system information and resource utilization using a graphical interface (Zenity).

It can:
.RS
.IP \(bu
Show CPU, RAM, disk, and GPU usage in real time.
.IP \(bu
Save periodic system data (CPU frequency, RAM, disk usage) to log files.
.IP \(bu
Allow users to configure refresh rates and durations.
.IP \(bu
Be configured via an external config.cfg file.
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Display this help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-v
Display the script version and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The script reads configuration values from a file named \fIconfig.cfg\fR located in the same directory. Example config:
.nf
REFRESH_RATE=2
LOG_DIR=./logs
VERSION=1.1
.fi

These values set:
.RS
.IP \(bu
REFRESH_RATE: Default refresh rate in seconds.
.IP \(bu
LOG_DIR: Directory where log files will be saved.
.IP \(bu
VERSION: Script version shown with \-v.
.RE
.SH FEATURES
.B Basic System Information
.br
Displays architecture, CPU details, frequencies, RAM info, and system kernel.

.B System Utilization
.br
Shows:
.RS
.IP \(bu
CPU usage over time.
.IP \(bu
RAM usage over time.
.IP \(bu
GPU VRAM usage (if available).
.IP \(bu
Disk space usage (all mounted filesystems).
.RE

.B Save log to file
.br
Asks user for interval and duration, then saves system data periodically to a log file named:
.nf
system_report_YYYYMMDD_HHMM.txt
.fi
inside the configured \fILOG_DIR\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.cfg
Configuration file for the script.
.TP
.I ram_usage.sh, cpu_usage.sh, gpu_usage.sh, save_log.sh
Source modules loaded by the main script.
